args: Do a collab with me, Elisanne!
Yeah! I'm working with everyone in\nthe castle, and you're next.
I'm still in an experimental period,\nbut I'm getting closer to creating\na brand new style.
I see. Well, I'm flattered to be asked,\nand certainly willing to help.
But I'm far from an expert in the field,\nso I doubt I would be of much practical\nuse.
Oh, I see... Still, there has to be SOME\nway we can work together.
Would you perhaps be interested in a\nbook of human art? I have one you're\nmore than welcome to borrow.
It is a collection of religious art;\nthe goddess herself, mythological\nsymbols, interpreted scripture.
Thinking on it more, you have likely\nnever seen such things before.\nIt may prove quite illuminating.
Oh man, I'd LOVE to borrow it.
Y-yes, well... Where was that book...
A Palaydn must be well-read—though\nmy passion for literature emerged well\nbefore I took up the lance.
Eh, not really. It takes time away\nfrom painting.
I suppose it does.\nAh—here we are.
If I can be of any more help,\nplease let me know.
This book should keep me busy for now\nthough. I wanna read it cover to cover.
I can only imagine what you will\ncreate once you've done so.
Heh heh, I'll come show you as\nsoon as I'm done!
Elisanne! Can I borrow another book?
Of course. What would you like to\nstudy next?
I was actually hoping this next one\ncould be a story book.
Up to now, I've only been painting things\nyou see in the forest—trees, flowers,\nthat kind of stuff.
I never thought of turning a story into a \npainting—so I wanna try it!
I thought I could maybe paint something\nfrom a story YOU like.
That sounds like a splendid idea.
I look forward to seeing what you produce.
Do you have a moment, Elly?\nI'd like to discuss some new\nstrategies.
I'll be back soon, Fleur—but please\nhelp yourself to any books that catch\nyour interest.
Perhaps one of them will spark your\nnext masterpiece.
Oh boy, I sure hope so!
Elisanne is super nice. I'm so glad we\ngot to collaborate!
Oh. But which books does she like?
Dang, I really should have asked before\nshe left. Hmm...
I mean, she's a Paladyn—this MUST\nbe one of her favs.

Let's see... ＂The Paladyn Creed: A Paladyn
must, at the behest of divine providence,
ply their seraphic blade to adjudge all
malignity and animus that bide...＂
I don't get this at all.
She must have something simpler... Hm?
What's this book in the corner?
What IS this?\nWho says ＂I'm gonna make you mine,\nbaby girl＂—and to a PRINCESS?
People aren't property!\n...Gah! Now he's stealing her\naway from the prince?!
This... This is kidnapping! Stop it!
They were going to be married in\nthe morning! GIVE HER BACK!
Was he mad 'cause he wasn't invited?\nI guess I understand that... Wait, no!\nStealing people is bad!
This book is making me MAD.\n...I wonder what's on the next page...
Did you find anything interesting, Fleur?
Are you all right?\nYou look flushed.
What are you... Wait.\nSurely that isn't—
It IS! How did you find that novel?\nI made a point of hiding it away.
On the lips... ON THE LIPS!
I-it's all right, Fleur. \nThe book can't hurt you anymore.\nYour poor young mind...
Goddess, I should have chosen some books\nfor her... Fleur, stay with me!
